Pete, Bryan and Philip are cousins. Pete's age is one-third of Bryan and Philip is five years elder than Bryan. If the sum of the age of the cousins is 40,find the ages of each.
A. 10, 15, 15
B. 15, 10, 15
C. 15, 15, 10
D. 10, 10, 15
E. 10, 15, 10
Let the age of Pete be x years.
Then, Bryan's age = 3x years and Philip's age = 5x + 5 years.
The sum of the ages of the cousins = 40 years.
=> 3x + 5x + 5 = 40
=> 8x = 40
=> x = 5 years
Hence, the ages of the cousins are 10, 15, 15 years.
